=== Pronunciation ===
[[Category:Hebrew language]]
אחר / 'achar / akh-ar'
=== Etymology ===

From {{HH|309}}; 
=== Noun ===
properly the hind part; generally used as an adverb or conjugation, after (in various senses): - after (that, -ward), again, at, away from, back (from, -side), behind, beside, by, follow (after, -ing), forasmuch, from, hereafter, hinder end, + out (over) live, + persecute, posterity, pursuing, remnant, seeing, since, thence [-forth], when, with.

[[fr:אחר]]